A Nigerian doctor has been assured of spiritual and physical protection against coronavirus after a good samaritan gave her a special facemask. The Donor who seems to be a strong christian, shared face shields which had the characters ”Psalm 91” boldly printed on it. Sharing the photo, the doctor with the Twitter handle Oyin_xO she wrote: “Someone donated face shields with Psalm 91 printed on it to the clinic today. Lmao love it” Below is an excerpt from the popular Bible chapter: “He who dwells in the shelter of the Most High will rest in the shadow of the Almighty. I will say of the LORD, “He is my refuge and my fortress, my God, in whom I trust.” … “Because he loves me,” says the LORD, “I will rescue him; I will protect him, for he acknowledges my name.” Source Even as virologists and other medical scientists are still grappling with a multiplicity of ideas to produce effective vaccines to tackle the novel COVID-19 that has wrestled humanity on its knees, a cleric says there is hope after all. In an interview with News Express, the cleric, Prophet Francis Onwudinwe… April 14, 2020 In "News" PREMIUM TIMES reports that the General Overseer of the Redeemed Christian Church of God, (RCCG), Enoch Adeboye, on Sunday said the current outbreak of COVID-19 across the world will soon subside but will not be ‘completely eradicated’. Mr Adeboye, who addressed his congregation across the globe via a live broadcast… March 22, 2020 In "News" Panda  -  A Christian cleric from Gombe State, Rev. Tortuman Danbauchi, on Sunday admonished Nigerians to always give thanks to God in spite of current economic recession. Danbauchi also urged Nigerians to appreciate God no matter the difficult situation they face. Danbauchi, who is the Chairman of Evangelical Church of West African… December 11, 2016 In "News"